A former Chairman, Projects Development Institute (PRODA) Enugu, Daniel Onjeh has joined the race for Benue South Senatorial seat under the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The ex-PRODA Chairman made the disclosure on Monday while addressing a crowd of supporters in Ogbadibo Local Government Area of the State “For the umpteenth time, I have thrown my hat into the ring to contest the Senate in 2023 and unlike the previous times that I’ve heeded this call, this time, it’s God’s appointed time, so, I shall be there,” he said. According to Onje, his aim of joining the race was to ensure a quality representation of people of the zone, expressing confidence that he would emerge winner of the senatorial battle in 2023. NAN reports that dignitaries at the event included Sen. Ameh Ebute, a former President of the Senate, Mr Abba Yaro, the immediate past State Chairman, among others. Recall that Onjeh was the APC candidate for the zone at the 2015 general election, where he lost to the then President of the Senate David Mark, who contested on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP.